    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/Gambella>
            a       <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#Region> ;
            <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                    "Gambella region (Ethiopia)" ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#description>
                    "Gambella is also officially known as Gambella Peoples' Region, is one of the nine ethnic divisions (kililoch) of Ethiopia. Previously known as 'Region 12', its capital is Gambella. The Region is situated between the Baro and Akobo Rivers, with its western part including the Baro salient. Located in Gambella is Gambella National Park, which covers approximately 5,061 square kilometers or 17% of the Region's territory." ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#geo>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/Gambella_Shape> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#partOf>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/Ethiopia> .
    
