    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/MINTPROJECT-PIHM%253AV2>
            a       <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#SoftwareImage> ;
            <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                    "mintproject/pihm:v2" ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#availableInRegistry>
                    "https://hub.docker.com/repository/docker/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
    
    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/46ce03cf-4e89-4d09-80b4-d34eca18f02e>
            a       <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#ModelConfigurationSetup> , <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#Theory-GuidedModel> , <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#ConfigurationSetup> ;
            <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                    "DroughtPredict_v1.0.0_eea_ecwmf" ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#author>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/khider_deborah> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#description>
                    "This setup uses the droughtpredict_eea configuration with version v1.0.0 of the model and consists of a deep learning model with three convolutional layers and one fully connected layer. \n\nThe model was trained on 1700 years of SPI data calculated from precipitation in the CESM control simulation and is only applicable to Eastern Equatorial Africa. Testing was performed on the 1981-2018 period in the EMCWF ERA5 reanalysis. The ECWMF EAR5 data was regridded to match the resolution of the CESM output for testing purposes. \n\nThe model uses the last three months available in the ECMWF ERA5 reanalysis dataset and makes predictions up to 4 months in advance. This setup fixes the input data to the ECMWF ERA5 file. \n." ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasAssumption>
                    "One of the major assumptions is that drought/precipitation is correctly represented in the CESM control simulation, which is used for training. Any biases in this physical model will propagate to the machine learning model. One such bias is its inability to fully capture the magnitude of extreme events." ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasConstraint>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/2b6e0acf-ae13-4e64-b344-47711c4c3f39> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasInput>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/d31bc2d7-b41d-4c27-ab45-ac2f3f2952fb> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasInstallationInstructions>
                    "To run in prediction mode, requires the pre-trained models and the Pytorch library" ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasOutput>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/b52b7e1d-f7a2-4d1f-b1c4-e27d9933ea8b> , <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/829372df-3aba-4621-bf0f-625724f84ba2> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasParameter>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/a43e8cdf-477e-475c-93cd-8cf7c41c143b> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasSoftwareImage>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/f39ba110-84d0-4908-861d-b6ca1ffcccec> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasUsageNotes>
                    "Accuracy varies between 0.4 to 0.8 as expressed through the Pearson's correlation coefficient. The accuracy varies both in space and with prediction lead time. Generally, accuracy decreases with lead time. At 4 months, the model converged to neutral state. \n\nVisualization of the accuracy can be found here: https://github.com/mintproject/DroughtPredictViz. Use the LaunchBinder badge." ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#keywords>
                    "Drought; Standardized Precipitation Index; SPI; Eastern Equatorial Africa; Deep Learning" ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#shortDescription>
                    "Deep learning model for SPI prediction in Eastern Equatorial Africa up to 4 months in advance." ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#tag>
                    "latest" ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#usefulForCalculatingIndex>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/standardized_precipitation_index> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#hasGrid>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/3bb63af6-9f57-4bca-8d02-863b53e4b1e1> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#hasModelCategory>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/Weather> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#hasOutputTimeInterval>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/c3af1de1-752b-40c9-a0d3-6da7c7ee2068> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#hasProcess>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/cycles_precipitation_process> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#hasRegion>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/Ethiopia> , <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/South_Sudan> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#parameterAssignmentMethod>
                    "Calibration" .
    
