            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#description>
                    "River discharge is the volume of water flowing through a river channel. This is the total volume of water flowing through a channel at any given point and is measured in cubic metres per second (cumecs). The discharge from a drainage basin depends on precipitation, evapotranspiration and storage factors (http://www.geography.learnontheinternet.co.uk/topics/discharge.html)" ;
