            a       <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#Region> ;
            <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                    "Muger basin (Ethiopia)" ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#description>
                    "The Muger River (or Mujer) is a north-flowing tributary of the Abay River in central Ethiopia, which is notable for its deep gorge. Its confluence with the Abay is at: 9Â°55?07N 37Â°55?50ECoordinates: 9Â°55?07N 37Â°55?50E. Tributaries of the Muger include the Labbu. The Muger has a drainage area of about 8,188 square kilometers." ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#geo>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/Muger_Shape> ;
            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sdm#partOf>
                    <https://w3id.org/okn/i/mint/Ethiopia> .
    
