            <https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasUsageNotes>
                    "There are 2 kinds of expert perturbation for parameters. The first is multiplicative to the parameter field as a fraction, for variables like precipitation (e.g., .9 <1< 1.1).  The second is additive to the field -2<0<+2. The additive case is for variables like temperature (e.g., 2 degrees greater or 2 degrees less)." ;
